page.title: 01Landcover
page.content: The highest moorland in the area is 1341 feet above sea level.On the top of the mountain the grass is dry and brown.Other plants that grow there are cord moss,heath and bilberry. We call the bilberry the whimberry. At about 1000 feet the land is wetter. It is peat bog covered with rushes, cord moss,heath and moorland grass. At the bottom of the valley and on its sides are farms.The farms have some woodland on them with trees like beech,oak,ash,rowan,alder,elder,birch, hawthorn,willow and sycamore.On the valley sides the Forestry Commision have planted sitka spruce and larch. Around our village there is a large area of reclaimed land.
